Key Match Events: Denmark advanced to the knockout phase of Euro 2024 thanks to a 0-0 draw with Serbia in Munich.
Rasmus Hojlund was subbed off midway through the second half.
Jonas Wind got himself booked in the first half and had to be withdrawn at the break.
Denmark will now face tournament hosts Germany in the round of 16 in Dortmund on Saturday night.
Serbia's coach Dragan Stojkovic made two half-time substitutions, bringing on Tadic and Jovic.
Post-Match Reflections: Kasper Hjulmand expressed happiness about advancing to the knockout stage and acknowledged areas for improvement in attack.
Dragan Stojkovic expressed disappointment over Serbia's failure to advance but praised his team's effort.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Novak Djokovic was present at the match to support Serbia, despite recovering from a knee injury.
